<paragraph id="CE0B36A63B16FF80FF779021FAC4FA25" blockId="9.[192,802,1807,1891]" lastBlockId="9.[830,1441,1302,1448]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="FCC0EAB43B16FF80FF779021FEE9F8AB" box="[192,305,1807,1830]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Comments</emphasis>
: The latter specimen (No. 3398) differs from the 
<typeStatus id="110F88043B16FF80FF5B9003FEFCF8C9" box="[236,292,1837,1860]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">types</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="09B44D253B16FF80FEE69003FE2BF8C9" authorityName="Kovarik" authorityYear="2004" box="[337,499,1837,1860]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Orthochirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zagrosensis">
<emphasis id="FCC0EAB43B16FF80FEE69003FE2BF8C9" box="[337,499,1837,1860]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">O. zagrosensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in coloration of the femur and patella of legs, which are yellow. However, the color of the pedipalps agrees with the 
<typeStatus id="110F88043B16FF80FB699238FACEFAA0" box="[1246,1302,1302,1325]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">types</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation id="568F2A233B16FF80FA9F9238FAA9FAA0" box="[1320,1393,1302,1325]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="8.[192,268,955,979]" captionTargetBox="[191,1472,191,919]" captionTargetId="figure-9@8.[192,1471,192,918]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 7: Orthochirus zagrosensis Kovařík, 2004, male holotype, dorsal aspect." pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Figs. 7</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="568F2A233B16FF80FCF7921BFC95FAC1" box="[832,845,1333,1356]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="8.[192,268,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[191,1472,1007,1871]" captionTargetId="figure-33@8.[192,1471,1008,1870]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 8: Orthochirus zagrosensis Kovařík, 2004, male from NMW, dorsal aspect." pageId="9" pageNumber="8">8</figureCitation>
) and also all other characters support the species identity. Taking into account the color variation known to occur in the genus (see Kovařík, 2004: 28), we are satisfied that the specimen is 
<taxonomicName id="09B44D253B16FF80FBCF92BFFACCFA25" authorityName="Kovarik" authorityYear="2004" box="[1144,1300,1425,1448]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Orthochirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zagrosensis">
<emphasis id="FCC0EAB43B16FF80FBCF92BFFACCFA25" box="[1144,1300,1425,1448]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">O. zagrosensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
